(1746, '&amp;quot;Startled&amp;quot; in front of people access to phishing websites', '"Startled"-in-front-of-people-access-to-phishing-websites', '', '1', '<p>There have been at least 155 million users unknowingly accessing phishing sites, and nearly 50% of which is cybercrime attacks.</p>', '&lt;p&gt;According to the latest analysis by Kaspersky Lab, almost half of the attacks on the Internet through phishing emails or fake websites in 2016 for the purpose of stealing money from the victim. Compared with 2015, the number of attacks in 2016 has increased more than 13%.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;news-image&quot; src=&quot;http://image.24h.com.vn/upload/1-2017/images/2017-02-23/1487831972-148783147294569-banking.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&amp;amp;#34;Giật m&amp;igrave;nh&amp;amp;#34; trước lượng người truy cập v&amp;agrave;o c&amp;aacute;c website lừa đảo - 1&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp; &amp;nbsp;Online banking is a target for cybercriminals to steal money.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; In 2016, Kaspersky Lab has detected 155 million users access multiple phishing sites are different. Of these, more than 73.5 million users hacked Financial: The number of bank cards, credit accounts, passwords, social network and login information for e-banking. Consequently, cyber criminals use this information to steal money from the victim.&amp;nbsp;Nadezhda Demidova, an analyst at Kaspersky Lab, said: &quot;Phishing finance remains one of the easiest ways to cybercrime for the illicit proceeds. You do not have to be programmers skilled and do not need to invest more money in infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;Of course, the majority of fraudulent schemes are easily detected and prevented, but in terms of the data we collected, many people are still caught off guard with financial data online, if not, we I did not recognize many attacks so in 2016 &quot;.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;To protect yourself against phishing attacks, Kaspersky Lab\'s experts recommend: - When making a payment online, check the website is legitimate or not. Connections can be safer when protected by https. - Always check the true extent of the email you received.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;When these emails ask you to do something urgent to change the password, the first thing is to be sure they are sent from legitimate sources and contact your bank or payment system representatives to verify the internal email solution. - Do not click on links in emails or websites that you doubt their authenticity. - Use security measures with technology reliably against phishing attacks based on user behavior.&lt;/p&gt;\n&lt;p&gt;This will help keep your computer recognize a fraudulent scheme and sophisticated even if they do not already exist in the database.&lt;/p&gt;', 1, 0, '', 0, '', '', '1487834238.jpg', '23022017141718', 0, 635, 1, 2, '2017-02-23 14:17:18', NULL, 142, NULL, 1),
